      </row>
      <row>
        <cell right="minor"><m>$r5</m></cell>
        <cell />
        <cell />
        <cell />
        <cell><mathInput name="p43" /></cell>
      </row>
    </tabular>
    <answer><award targetsAreResponses="p00 p12 p24 p31 p43">
      <when matchPartial>
        <boolean><math simplify>mod($p00,5)</math>=<math simplify>mod($r1*$r1,5)</math> and 
        ($p00=$r1 or $p00=$r2 or $p00=$r3 or $p00=$r4 or $p00=$r5)</boolean> and
        <boolean><math simplify>mod($p12,5)</math>=<math simplify>mod($r2*$r3,5)</math> and 
        ($p12=$r1 or $p12=$r2 or $p12=$r3 or $p12=$r4 or $p12=$r5)</boolean> and
        <boolean><math simplify>mod($p24,5)</math>=<math simplify>mod($r3*$r5,5)</math> and 
        ($p24=$r1 or $p24=$r2 or $p24=$r3 or $p24=$r4 or $p24=$r5)</boolean> and
        <boolean><math simplify>mod($p31,5)</math>=<math simplify>mod($r4*$r2,5)</math> and 
        ($p31=$r1 or $p31=$r2 or $p31=$r3 or $p31=$r4 or $p31=$r5)</boolean> and
        <boolean><math simplify>mod($p43,5)</math>=<math simplify>mod($r5*$r4,5)</math> and 
        ($p43=$r1 or $p43=$r2 or $p43=$r3 or $p43=$r4 or $p43=$r5)</boolean>
      </when>
    </award></answer>
  </p>
  <p>
    <alert>Final Remark:</alert>
    In general, we will work with the standard set of transverals, but don't think that it is the only way to perform these computations!
    Sometimes it is much easier to use the "centered" set, or the 1-indexed set, etc..., and in rare instances, some really unusual choice of representatives of each possible remainder may make some incredibly difficult computation or proof much easier!
  </p>
